SIMPLE: fescue
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fescue
<hw>Fes"cue</hw> <pr>(f⟦ecr⟧s"k⟦usl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>festu</ets>, OF. <ets>festu</ets>, F. <ets>f⟦eacute⟧tu</ets>, fr.
L. <ets>festuca</ets> stalk, straw.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A straw,
wire, stick, etc., used chiefly to point out letters to children when
learning to read.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Pedantic <xex>fescue</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Sterne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To come under the <qex>fescue</qex> of an imprimatur.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An instrument for playing on the harp; a
plectrum.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chapman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The style of a dial.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A grass of the genus
<gen>Festuca</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Fescue grass</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a genus of
grasses (<gen>Festuca</gen>) containing several species of importance in
agriculture. <spn>Festuca ovina</spn> is <stype>sheep's fescue</stype>;
<spn>F. elatior</spn> is <stype>meadow fescue</stype>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fescue</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fescue
<hw>Fes"cue</hw> <pr>(f⟦ecr⟧s"k⟦usl⟧)</pr>, <pos>v. i. & t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Fescued</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>;
<pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Fescuing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To
use a fescue, or teach with a fescue.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fesels</ent>⟦br⟧
